</small></span>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>1948: The first doctoral thesis about radio in Quebec is defended at
the
Universit&eacute; de Paris-Sorbonne by Jacques Beauchamp-Forget. <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1948: The Institut de la Radio is founded at Laval University,
attached to
the Service ext&eacute;rieur de la Facult&eacute; des Sciences
sociales, headed by <span style="">&nbsp;</span>Napol&eacute;on
Leblanc and Aur&egrave;le S&eacute;guin. <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1949: <span style="">&nbsp;</span>The federal government creates
the Royal Commission on National Development in the Arts, Letters and
Sciences,
under the chairmanship of Vincent Massey with Georges-Henri
L&eacute;vesque as
co-chair.<o:p></o:p></p>
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">1950:
<span style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;">The following 16
stations </span><a name="n3"><span
 style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;">open during the 1950s</span><sup><span
 style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;"> </span>[</sup></a><sup><a
