CJAF (Cabano, 1960), CJLM (Joliette, 1960), CKBS (Saint-Hyacinthe,
1960), CHLC
(Hauterive, 1962), CKLM (Laval, 1962), CJFM-MF (Montreal, 1962), CFMB
(Montreal,
angl., 1962), CKGM-MF (Montreal, angl., 1963), CKML (Mont-Laurier,
1964), CKMF
(Montreal, 1964), CFQR (Montreal, 1966), CFLS (L&eacute;vis, 1967),
CHVD (Dolbeau,
1967), CHLT-FM (Sherbrooke, 1967, qui devient CITE-FM en 1976), CJRP
(Qu&eacute;bec,
1969), CJMD (Chibougamau, 1969), <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1961: Creation of the provincial ministry of cultural affairs<span
 style=""> <span lang="FR-CA">(Minist&egrave;re des Affaires
culturelles du Qu&eacute;bec). <o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
<p>1962: Start of radio courses in spoken French, music, and English,
offered
by the D&eacute;partement de l'Instruction publique du Qu&eacute;bec. <o:p></o:p></p>
<p><span style="" lang="FR-CA">1964: Creation of the
ministry of education, (Minist&egrave;re de l'&Eacute;ducation du
Qu&eacute;bec). <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>1965: Gilles Vigneault sings "Mon Pays" for the first time.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p><span style="" lang="FR-CA">1966: Founding of the
contemporary music association, the <i>Soci&eacute;t&eacute; de
musique contemporaine du
Qu&eacute;bec</i>. <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
</p>
<p>1967: World&#8217;s Fair in Montreal called "Man and His World", numerous
heads of state visit the city, the number of live broadcasts increases
exponentially. <o:p></o:p></p>
<o:p></o:p>
<p>1968: The federal government adopts a law creating the Canadian
Radio and
Television Council (CRTC). <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1969: The Quebec government creates its communications ministry, the
Minist&egrave;re
des Communications. <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1969: The 1945 law is modified and the Office de la
radio-t&eacute;l&eacute;vision du
Qu&eacute;bec is created, with a mandate to broadcast educational
programming. <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1969: The Radiomutuel network is created by Raymond Cr&eacute;peault
(Corporation
Civitas Radiomutuel). <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1970: During the 1970s, <span style="">&nbsp;</span>41 stations <a
 name="n5">open, including<sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
