<p>1978: The Quebec government, under the authority of minister Camille
Laurin,
publishes a cultural development policy entitled "La Politique
qu&eacute;b&eacute;coise
du d&eacute;veloppement culturel". <o:p></o:p></p>
<p>1979: At the end of the decade, the "open lines" account for 17% of
broadcast hours overall, but CFCF gives them 47%, CKVL 22% and the
others
between 8% and 12%. <o:p></o:p></p>
