<p align="center"><font size="2"><font size="2">&nbsp;</font></font></p>
<h2><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><big><big><span
 style="font-weight: bold;"><a
 name="Radio_broadcasting_in_Quebec_in_1997"></a>Radio
broadcasting in Quebec in 1997</span></big></big> <o:p></o:p></span></h2>
<p>75 years after the beginnings of radio in this city, Montreal counts
about 182
stations <a name="n8"><sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n8"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">8</span></a>]</sup>:
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>27 FM community radio <span style="">&nbsp;</span><a name="n9">stations
<sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n9"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">9</span></a>]</sup>,
<br>
81 commercial <a name="n11"><sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n11"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">11</span></a>]</sup>
stations <a name="n10"><sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n10"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">10</span></a>]</sup>
<br>
13 Radio-Canada government stations <a name="n12"><sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n12"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">12</span></a>]</sup>
<br>
1 Radio-Canada International <a name="n13">station<sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n13"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">13</span></a>]</sup><br>
10 FM student radio <a name="n14">stations <sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n14"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">14</span></a>]</sup>
<br>
50 Native stations <a name="n15"><sup>[</sup></a><sup><a
 href="/radio/reperesnotes-eng.html#n15"><span
 style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none;">15</span></a>].</sup>
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>--Pierre Pag&eacute;, Professor at UQAM <o:p></o:p></p>
